  "prompt": "Do VoLTE calls work with data switched off?",
  "response": "VoLTE (Voice over LTE) calls typically require that mobile data is switched on, even if you are not actively using data for other applications. VoLTE uses the LTE network for voice calls rather than traditional circuits used in older networks, which fundamentally relies on a data connection to transmit voice information. However, you don't need to be actively using mobile data for other applications during a VoLTE call; your phone will manage the data usage automatically for the voice call itself.\n\nIf your mobile data is turned off, you may fall back to other services, such as circuit-switched voice calls (if your carrier supports that) or potentially 3G/2G networks if available.",
